e infrastructure is notably absent in much of the country, leading to an overall climate of insecurity. Haiti: Hope for a Fragile State sheds light on the varied and complex roots of the current crisis, dispels misperceptions, and suggests that the situation in Haiti, despite evidence to the contrary, is not completely desperate. It brings together diverse perspectives on development, the military, history, NGOs, and politics and discusses the peace-building efforts of the past, suggesting ways to move forward to make Haiti a strong state. Co-published with the Centre for International Governance Innovation  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHistory. 4aPolitical Science. 7aHISTORY / Caribbean & West Indies / General.2bisacsh1 aCastor, Suzy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDade, Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFatton, Robert Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgson, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaguire, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorneau, Col. Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShamsie, Yasmine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShamsie, Yasmine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aThompson, Andrew S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, Andrew S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458132040uhttps://www.degruyt